				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">At first it seems inferior to the simple parallel interfaces of systems like Atari and Master System, but those don't offer endless possibilities of how to write (and optimize [and mis-optimize])) the controller reading code. And the serial interface lends itself to easy expansion, for example the SNES controller and being able to easily wire it to a NES.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

