					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Actually the chain ends at the 6-pad, the multitaps are <em>not</em> compatible (well, except maybe EA's to some extent since it behaves as a port multiplexer). But yeah, Sega managed to extend the protocol quite far, and in fact the way the 6-pad protocol works effectively gives it infinite permutations (since it advances by bit toggling).</div>

